MayaPS: A system for typing Ancient Maya glyphs with TeX/LaTeX

Authors:  Stepan Orevkov  (TeX tools)
          Bruno  Delprat  (Maya fonts)

version 1.1b, March 5, 2017

To extract files (Linux/MacOS) type:

  tar -xf mayaps-1-1.tar.gz

(all files will be extractet into the current directory)

doc/mayaps-d.pdf  detailed reference manual
doc/*-map.pdf     tables of glyphs in available Maya fonts (font maps)
doc-scr/          source files for mayaps-d.pdf (can be used as an example)
makefont.tar      tool for creating new mayaps fonts (see mayaps-d.pdf, Sect.12.2)

To use makefont, extract it by

  tar -xf makefont.tar

and see makefont/README-m

--------------------
All files here are the same as in version 1.0 (December 2012) except:
  mayaps.tex
  mayaps.pro
  mayaps-d.tex (in doc-src.tar)
  mayaps-d.pdf
  cotrace.c    (in makefont.tar)
  README

